sql:
SELECT SUM(wins) AS total_wins
FROM team_performance
WHERE team_id = 0 AND season_id = 0;

SELECT COUNT(g.game_id) AS total_games_played
FROM games g
WHERE g.team_id = 0 AND g.season_id = 0;

SELECT winning_percentage
FROM team_performance
WHERE team_id = 1 AND season_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- Teams with more than one player are considered;
- Total points scored by all players on each team are summed up;
- Teams are ranked by the total points scored, with the highest-scoring team listed first.

- The NBA (National Basketball Association) is a professional basketball league in North America;
- The 2023 Regular Season refers to the main part of the NBA season, typically lasting from October to April;
- Points scored are a key metric in basketball, reflecting a team's offensive performance.

- The overall performance score is calculated as 2 times points scored, 1.5 times assists, 1 times rebounds, minus 0.5 times turnovers;
- The average winning percentage is calculated by averaging the winning percentages of all teams in the league;
- The query aims to find the player who not only excels individually but also contributes to a successful team;
- The player must have an overall performance score and team winning percentage above the league averages.

sql:
SELECT league_id, league_name, founded_year, league_logo, COUNT(*) AS occurrence_count
FROM leagues
GROUP BY league_id, league_name, founded_year, league_logo;

